
Alembic migration environment for ai_chatbot_code_challenge.

## Usage

Alembic reads the database connection from the application's settings, which assemble the URL from component variables.

### Local development
Set your local database settings:

```sh
export DATABASE_HOST=localhost
export DATABASE_PORT=5432
export DATABASE_USER=chatbot
export DATABASE_PASSWORD=chatbotpass
export DATABASE_NAME=chatbotdb
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Initial migration"
alembic upgrade head
```

### Docker/Compose
Set your Docker Compose database settings (Compose overrides host to `db` for the app):

```sh
export DATABASE_HOST=db
export DATABASE_PORT=5432
export DATABASE_USER=chatbot
export DATABASE_PASSWORD=chatbotpass
export DATABASE_NAME=chatbotdb
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Initial migration"
alembic upgrade head
```

Alembic will use the correct database depending on your environment.
